Here's a summary of TUnit's lifecycle hooks at each scope:

---

## 1. Before/After every test in a class

```csharp
public class OrderTests
{
    [Before(Test)]
    public async Task ResetDatabase(TestContext context)
    {
        await InMemoryDb.ResetAsync();
    }

    [After(Test)]
    public async Task Cleanup(TestContext context)
    {
        // optional per-test teardown
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task Order_MustHaveItems() { /* ... */ }
}
```

You can also use a **constructor** and `IAsyncDisposable.DisposeAsync`.

---

## 2. Once before/after all tests in a class (class-scoped fixture)

```csharp
public class IntegrationTests
{
    private static ServiceFixture _fixture = null!;

    [Before(Class)]
    public static async Task OpenFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        _fixture = await ServiceFixture.CreateAsync();
    }

    [After(Class)]
    public static async Task DisposeFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        await _fixture.DisposeAsync();
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task Can_Query_Service() { /* use _fixture */ }
}
```

Note: class-level hooks must be **static**.

---

## 3. Once before/after all tests in the assembly

```csharp
public static class AssemblySetup
{
    internal static WireMockServer Server = null!;

    [Before(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StartWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        Server = WireMockServer.Start();
    }

    [After(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StopWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        Server.Stop();
    }
}
```

---

## 4. Once for the entire test session (across all assemblies)

```csharp
public static class GlobalSetup
{
    [Before(TestSession)]
    public static async Task ApplyMigrations(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        await Database.MigrateAsync();
    }

    [After(TestSession)]
    public static async Task TearDownDatabase(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        await Database.DropAsync();
    }
}
```

---

### Quick reference

| Scope | Before | After |
|-------|--------|-------|
| Each test | `[Before(Test)]` | `[After(Test)]` |
| Class (once) | `[Before(Class)]` (static) | `[After(Class)]` (static) |
| Assembly (once) | `[Before(Assembly)]` (static) | `[After(Assembly)]` (static) |
| Session (once) | `[Before(TestSession)]` (static) | `[After(TestSession)]` (static) |

**Bonus:** `[BeforeEvery(Test)]` / `[AfterEvery(Test)]` are global cross-cutting hooks that fire for *every* test regardless of class — handy for logging or global diagnostics. All hooks can be `async Task` and accept an optional `CancellationToken` parameter.
